      "side": 0,
      "message": "I made slight algorithmic change here, since I believe the current code is slightly incorrect.\n\nImagine we attempted a transaction that touches entity E1. The transaction failed to land, we retried it, and this time it touched entity E2.\n\nBefore my change the code would:\n1. Lock(E1)\n2. Lock(E2)\n3. Drop([E2]).\n\nAfter my change it would Drop([E1, E2]).\n\nIt\u0027s not a big deal. Locks expire after a while, and while they are held all Getters go through slow code path and hit datastore directly. In general I found dscache to be pretty sloppy in how it treats locks :(",
